<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Somewhat variable in the density of the indumentum. It differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremnobrocha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea eremnobrocha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the narrower, acute, mucronate outer sepals. It is generally more densely hirsute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hinton</emphasis>
8120 (K) from Acatitlan, Temascaltepec is correctly identified as this species but the location would appear to be wrong. There was perhaps an error in the labelling.
</paragraph>
